quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  11,121,"And say to those who do not believe, "
  11,122,"And wait; indeed, we are waiting."
  11,123,"And to Allāh belong the unseen [aspects] of the heavens and the earth and to Him will be returned the matter, all of it, so worship Him and rely upon Him. And your Lord is not unaware of that which you do."
  12,82,"And ask the city in which we were and the caravan in which we came - and indeed, we are truthful.'"
  12,83,"[Jacob] said, "
  12,84,"And he turned away from them and said, ",footnotes:1:[i.e., he lost his sight.],footnotes:2:[He did not express the extent of his grief or his anger at what he suspected his sons had done but was patient, depending only upon Allāh for help.]
  14,28,"Have you not considered those who exchanged the favor of Allāh for disbelief{1} and settled their people [in] the home of ruin?",footnotes:1:They met Allāh's blessing with denial instead of gratitude.
  14,29,"[It is] Hell, which they will [enter to] burn, and wretched is the settlement."
  14,30,"And they have attributed to Allāh equals to mislead [people] from His way. Say, "
  15,1,"Alif, Lām, Rā.{1} These are the verses of the Book and a clear Qur’ān [i.e., recitation].",footnotes:1:See footnote to 2:1.
  15,2,"Perhaps those who disbelieve will wish{1} that they had been Muslims.",footnotes:1:On the Day of Judgement or at the time of death.
  15,3,"Let them eat and enjoy themselves and be diverted by [false] hope, for they are going to know."
